theorem Topology.isOpen_compl_boundary {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    IsOpen ((closure A \ interior A)ᶜ) := by
  -- Rewrite the complement of the boundary using a previously established lemma.
  have h_eq :
      ((closure A \ interior A)ᶜ) = interior A ∪ (closure A)ᶜ := by
    simpa using
      Topology.compl_boundary_eq_union_interior_compl_closure (X := X) (A := A)
  -- Both components of the union on the right are open.
  have h_open_int : IsOpen (interior A) := isOpen_interior
  have h_open_compl : IsOpen ((closure A)ᶜ) :=
    (isClosed_closure : IsClosed (closure A)).isOpen_compl
  -- The union of two open sets is open.
  have h_open_union : IsOpen (interior A ∪ (closure A)ᶜ) :=
    h_open_int.union h_open_compl
  -- Transfer the openness back to the original set via the equality `h_eq`.
  simpa [h_eq] using h_open_union

theorem Topology.closure_closure_diff_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    closure (closure A \ interior A) = closure A \ interior A := by
  -- The set `closure A \ interior A` is closed, hence equal to its closure.
  have hClosed : IsClosed (closure A \ interior A) :=
    Topology.isClosed_closure_diff_interior (X := X) (A := A)
  simpa using hClosed.closure_eq
